        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 11:29AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 1129 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a  cluster of strong
thunderstorms near and west of Wharton, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southwestern Rosenberg, El Campo, Wharton, Needville, East Bernard,
Ganado, Wallis, Simonton, Beasley, Kendleton, Orchard, Pierce,
Boling-Iago, Cordele, Damon, Egypt, Louise, Hungerford, Nada, and
Garwood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
